post_text:
The 2020 Census is happening now - responding is our civic duty and it matters for the future of every community. When you respond to the census, you do your part to make sure we have funding for the services and infrastructure we all count on - healthcare, education, even our roads, the funding all ties back to the census. In fact, Arizona stands to lose more than $3,000 per person every year for individuals that don‚Äôt respond - that‚Äôs funding that could go directly to making our communities stronger.

Responding to the census is safe and it just takes a few minutes. If you haven‚Äôt responded yet, take a few minutes to get it done online at my2020census.gov, by phone at 844.330.2020, or by sending back the form you received at your home. You‚Äôll skip the visit from a census worker and you‚Äôll help shape the next decade in our state. Be counted, Arizona!
#huskypride #caurus2020 #2020census

Hello Families,

Next week (March 30th-April 3rd) we are going to be doing a Virtual Spirit Week. This is a fun way for students and teachers to show their Husky Spirit while being at home.

The process is simple: First dress up according to each day, then take a picture of your child and post it online by tagging Caurus Academy on Facebook or @caurusacademy01 on Instagram. You can also direct message to either account to have your photo posted directly on our pages throughout the day.

Keep this schedule handy so you know what to dress up as or follow our pages to see a daily post on what to dress up as.

We are so excited to see your smiling faces showing us your Husky Spirit from home.

Love,
Caurus Academy

post_text:
Before we start our first day of distance learning tomorrow, I thought that I would share just one of the many TEDtalks that we use in professional development. As this may not pertain to our immediate population of students, the messaging, inspiration, and purpose behind being a champion for every student holds true. As you assist us in educating your students through distance learning, please know that your students have and deserve a few champions in their lives. Thank you for allowing us at Caurus to be them for your students!

Mr Blair

Rita F. Pierson: Every kid needs a champion https://www.ted.com/talks/rita_pierson_every_kid_needs_a_champion

We will be running one week after school martial arts program at Caurus! All students are welcome to attend this fun and exciting program. No experience needed, as this program costs $5, and all proceeds will go back to your child's school.

The program will run from Monday, 3/2 until Friday, 3/6 from 3:20-3:50pm AT CAURUS. Classes will focus on anti-bullying, predator defense, character development and fitness!

All classes will be taught by 25-year veteran certified instructors and owners of Phoenix Krav Maga and Fitness in Anthem. For any other program questions please text or call 815-484-3690.

Every year, the second graders at Maple Glen Elementary School, in Westfield, Indiana read all about Flat Stanley and his adventures around the world. The students then make flat versions of themselves and send them out, in the mail, to friends and relatives to have adventures of their own.

Caurus Academy High School had the pleasure of hosting Flat Kambelle for a day! She went to a bunch of classes like: Speech & Debate, Dual Enrollment English and even Geometry! The best part was going to watch the Huskies in action at the Varsity Boy‚Äôs Basketball game!

After her adventures at Caurus, Flat Kambelle was mailed back home to Indiana with a few souvenirs to show her friends in Mrs. Bruch‚Äôs class. Thank you Mrs. Bruch for this opportunity!!

Open Enrollment begins on January 6, 2020 at 7:30am on both the K-5 and Middle/High School campuses. Accepting applications for grades K-12 for the 2020-2021 academic year, we anticipate waitlists in several grade levels so get your application in today.
